==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Miriam'''

# Sister of [[Moses]] and [[Aaron]]. She was born in Egypt when the Jews were kept as slaves by the Egyptians. Cf. [[myrrhe]].
# A female [[given name]]. [[Maria]] is the Greek form of this name.

===Etymology===
Hebrew: [[מרים|מִרְיָם]] (Miriam), from Aramaic ''[[מרים]]'' (Maryām), bitter, from a root '''מר''' (<small>MR</small>) meaning "to be bitter".

